{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id77a157f0-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s450bb–2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"450bb–2"},"text":"§ 450bb–2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Maintenance of museum; acceptance of museum articles; construction of roads, etc.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary is authorized to—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77a157f1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s450bb–2/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Maintain, either in an existing structure acquired under the provisions of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s450bb"},"text":"section 450bb of this title","children":[],"tail":" or in a building constructed by him for the purpose, a museum for relics and records pertaining to historic events that took place at Harpers Ferry, and for other relics of national and patriotic interest, and to accept on behalf of the United States, for installation in such museum, articles which may be offered as additions to the museum;"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77a157f2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s450bb–2/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Construct roads and facilities and mark with monuments, tablets, or otherwise, points of interest within the boundaries of the Harpers Ferry National Historical Park; and","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id77a157f3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s450bb–2/3"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"3"},"text":"(3)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Provide, directly or by contract, subject to the provisions of the Act of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-06-07"},"text":"June 7, 1974","children":[],"tail":", an interpretive shuttle transportation service within, between, and among lands acquired for the purpose of sections 450bb to 450bb–2 of this title for such times and upon such terms as in his judgment will best accomplish the purposes of sections 450bb to 450bb–2 of this title."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id77a157f4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-06-30/ch328/s3"},"text":"June 30, 1944, ch. 328, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/646"},"text":"58 Stat. 646","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/33"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–33","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1963-05-29"},"text":"May 29, 1963","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/52"},"text":"77 Stat. 52","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/466/s1/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–466, § 1(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1974-10-24"},"text":"Oct. 24, 1974","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1420"},"text":"88 Stat. 1420","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/108/307/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 108–307, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2004-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 2004","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/118/1134"},"text":"118 Stat. 1134","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id77a157f5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id77a157f6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"